  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study hypothesis is that follow up from general practitioner after hospitalization for
      self poisoning will decrease suicidal behaviour.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients hospitalized after an episode of self poisoning will be randomly assigned into
      intervention an control groups. The intervention is close follow up by general practitioner
      six months. Both groups will receive treatment as usual.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
